<br>
Plot: Final Fantasy X is about a summoner named Yuna, whos on a pilgrimage to stop a evil force called Sin from destroying the world. You play out the main character Tidus and join her among with a couple others to guide her to obtain the final Aeon that will destroy sin. Its pretty straight forward throughout the whole game, with a few twists in it but thats a change in this series, usually its something small at first Example FF7 *Help Avalanche stop Shin-ra, Turns into Stop Sephiroth* I wont say much about it because the rest would spoil.<br>
<br>
Characters: This game finally beat the characters of FF6 for me, Tidus topped Locke, who i considered to be the coolest character in the series. Tidus is cheerful (thank god no fag daddie Squallers loner kid mcgee, Or Cloud Hi im a mental nut, Or Zidane hi im a retard) Tidus is witty, funny, and all around a great character. Yuna, the games lead female, Is very sweet, quiet, strong willed, and pretty. Lulu, a guardian of Yuna keeps to herself alot, is somewhat of a smartass sometimes, and is a black magic user who kicks major ass. Wakka was great, He is also a guardian of Yuna, hes not too bright when it comes to some things, but that is what makes him funny. He sees Tidus as a younger brother, is a strong believer in his faith, and is captain of a blitzball team. <br>
Kimahri is another one of yunas  guardians, who doesn't speak much but is devoted to Yuna entirely. Rikku is the Selphie type of this game, but not AS annoying. And Lastly Auron, Who is my second favorite of the game. Hes this ones Mysterious type *Shadow, Vincent, Amarant etc* But hes wise, somewhat of a mentor to Tidus and the best fighter in the party.<br>
<br>
English Voice acting: I was, at first worried that this game would suffer the fate of games such as Grandia 2, but no. Thank god, Square did this right. The voices fit the characters perfectly, the acting is grade A, Nothing over dramatic *whew* Tidus' voice cracks at times, but keep in mind hes 17 years old *I'm 19, and from time to time mine does too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> * <br>
<br>
Music/sound effects: Well... Some of it was the best i've heard in a FF game, and some of it lacked entirely. My personal favorites where the Battle theme which i think is the best next to FF7s, The otherworld theme, And Tidus' Theme. Some i didnt really like where the temple theme, and The boss theme. The sound effects where prefect. From Sword slashes, to Wakkas Blitzballs being pegged off baddies.<br>
<br>
Mini-games: Simply the best i've played, Blitzball is mad fun once you learn it. And the little mini games along the way are cool too such as attempting to preform the Jecht shot *You'll find out*<br>
<br>
SubQuests: Good god.... They add at least another 40-50 hours to the game. Most are worth the time as well.<br>
<br>
Battle System. Often people complain about this since FF5. I must say i was happy with the newer system granted i didnt have problems with the old one as some people did. Its turn based which is kinda cool, in some battles you'll have to use certain characters which get Trigger commands, and you can use them to stun the enemy, or knock something over to crush them. Theres more Strategy in battles then in past FF games thank god. It took me a few hours to figure out how to beat the last boss *If your having problems E-mail me at Kenshinhimura19@hotmail.com and i will help ya some*<br>
<br>
The Sphere Grid: This is the method for raising your characters stats. No longer do you gain exp and level up. Instead you gain AP *Ability points* which allow you to gain Sphere levels. 1 Sphere level = 1 move on the grid. the Grid is laid out for you so you should take a look at it to see which areas contain the stuff which you want your characters to learn / be better at. Each character starts off in their own place which suits them, but later in the game for instance Tidus, whose area of the grid is mostly balanced out *Speed, Strength, HP, MP, etc) You may want him to become pure melee, so you'd move him into Aurons section which is mostly composed of HP, Strength, and defense, or maybe you want him to learn some black magic so you'd move him into Lulus area... its your choice you customize your characters which is pretty cool *i hated the Junction/draw system with a passion*<br>
<br>
Replay value: Im playing it again right after beating it put it that way. 2nd time is seeming better then the 1st.<br>
<br>
